are 60 miles deep in the Ozark mts. the most beautiful scenery you could im-agine. Branson is a town up 1100 about eight years old. the White-rover voted for its beautiful scenery has been dammed making a lake 40 miles long, it is a summer resort and the shore on the <unclear/> side is dotted with Bungalows, steamboats come and go every day. In the summer it is a regular gala place. John bought a house and four and one half acres 1/4 of a mile from the lake west and up a hill all the way. the most rise 300 feet in that distance. The house has six rooms finished and one up stairs to be finished the rooms are <unclear/> very large. I have the down stiars bed room furnished with my things and wil occupy it until I build or buy just at present I think I shall build on 2 acres of John's East of him facing South. the land is rocky but grows every kind here is young yet. plenty of old orchards but all run down because no one cared enough to take care of them. The natives are 2 shifters set. drawl out their words and they work the same way. I never saw so many cows roming over the hills mostly jerseys. The grazing is good most all winter. We have had 20 <unclear/>. Pics go out every day. Persimmons are plentiful and so good. Passions and coons too. John has bought his a Jersey Cow 